body: A little over a month later, on the 30th of December 1998 at Comiket 55, Touhou 5 Mystic Square, also known as Kaikidan would be released. It started development sometime in 1998, and finished development sometime after the 21st of November 1998. It is unknown how many copies Touhou 5 approximately sold, but if it followed the trend of it going up every new entry in the series then it either sold more than Touhou 4, or sold around as much as Touhou 4. Touhou 5 was released exclusively for the PC-98.
On the 21st of November 1998, ZUN released a trial version of the 5th Touhou game

A little over a month later, on the 14th of August 1998 at Comiket 54, Touhou 4 Lotus Land Story, also known as Gensoukyou would be released. It started development sometime during 1998, and finished development sometime after the 2nd of July 1998. Touhou 4 sold approximately 200 - 300 copies. It was released exclusively for the PC-98.
On the 2nd of July 1998, ZUN released a trial version of the 4th Touhou game
